1.Remove default python binding if present:
	sudo apt-get purge python-opencv

2.Install and build opencv-2.4.10
	http://docs.opencv.org/doc/tutorials/introduction/linux_install/linux_install.html#linux-installation
	http://www.samontab.com/web/2014/06/installing-opencv-2-4-9-in-ubuntu-14-04-lts/

3.Extra dependencies
	sudo apt-get install libgstreamer1.0-dev libgstreamer-plugins-base1.0-dev libgstreamer0.10-dev libgstreamer-plugins-base0.10-dev

4.Build and install opencv-3.0.0-beta
	http://milq.github.io/install-opencv-ubuntu-debian/
	this one seems more reliable
	http://rodrigoberriel.com/2014/10/installing-opencv-3-0-0-on-ubuntu-14-04/
